* 1971: [[Academy Award]] winner (as a member of the Beatles)
* 18-time [[Grammy Award]] winner:
** Nine as a member of the Beatles
** Six as a solo artist
** Two as a member of Wings
** One as part of a joint collaboration
* Two-time inductee – [[Rock and Roll Hall of Fame]]:
** Class of 1988 as a member of the Beatles
** Class of 1999 as a solo artist
* [[Order of the British Empire|Member of the Order of the British Empire]].{{sfn|London Gazette|1965|pp=5487–5489}}{{sfn|Spitz|2005|p=556}}
* Planet [[4148 McCartney|4148]] named "McCartney" ([[International Astronomical Union]]'s [[Minor Planet Center]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.minorplanetcenter.net/iau/special/rocknroll/0004148.html |title= Minor planet number 4148 has been named in honor of former Beatle Paul McCartney |publisher=IAU Minor Planet Center |accessdate=9 March 2010}}</ref>
* 1988: Honorary [[Doctor of the University]] degree from [[University of Sussex]].<ref name="Sussex">{{Cite web |url=https://www.sussex.ac.uk/webteam/gateway/file.php?name=list-of-honorary-graduates.pdf&site=76 |title=University of Sussex Honorary Degrees Committee List of Honorary Graduates |last=Anon |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160119063525/https://www.sussex.ac.uk/webteam/gateway/file.php?name=list-of-honorary-graduates.pdf&site=76 |archivedate=19 January 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>
* 1997: [[Knight Bachelor|Knighted]] by [[Queen Elizabeth II]] for services to music.{{sfn|Badman|1999|p=563}}
* 2000: Fellowship into the [[British Academy of Songwriters, Composers and Authors]].{{sfn|Harry|2002|pp=38, 242}}
* 2008: [[BRIT Award]] for Outstanding Contribution to Music
* 2008: Honorary [[Doctor of Music]] degree from [[Yale University]].<ref>For the Brit Award, see: {{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/news/brit-awards-2008/34542|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080302115908/http://www.nme.com/news/brit-awards-2008/34542|archivedate=2 March 2008 |title=Sir Paul McCartney picks up special Brit award in London |work=NME |date=20 February 2008 |accessdate=3 May 2012}}; For the honorary degree from Yale, see: {{cite news|url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/life/music/2008-05-26-3778562167_x.htm |title=Yale gives Paul McCartney honorary music degree |work=USA Today |date=26 May 2008 |accessdate=3 May 2012}}</ref>
* 2010: [[Gershwin Prize]] for his contributions to popular music.<ref>{{cite news |last= Pareles |first= Jon |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2010/06/03/arts/music/03mccartney.html?src=mv |title= McCartney Is Honored at White House |work= The New York Times |date= 2 June 2010 |accessdate= 4 May 2012 |deadurl= no |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20130514081942/http://www.nytimes.com/2010/06/03/arts/music/03mccartney.html?src=mv |archivedate= 14 May 2013 |df= dmy-all }}</ref>
* 2010: [[Kennedy Center Honors]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/12/06/us/06honors.html/|title=Glittering Tributes for Winners of Kennedy Center Honors|last1=Becker|first1=Bernie|last2=Southall|first2=Ashley|work=The New York Times|date=5 December 2010|accessdate=7 July 2012|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150103223955/http://www.nytimes.com/2010/12/06/us/06honors.html|archivedate=3 January 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
* 2012: Star on the [[Hollywood Walk of Fame]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Sinha |first=Piya |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2012/02/10/us-paulmccartney-star-idUSTRE81902K20120210 |title=Paul McCartney finally gets Walk of Fame star |agency=Reuters |date=9 February 2012 |accessdate=9 February 2012 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120210133500/http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/02/10/us-paulmccartney-star-idUSTRE81902K20120210 |archivedate=10 February 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>
* 2012: [[Légion d'Honneur]] for his services to music.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-207_162-57508880/paul-mccartney-awarded-french-legion-of-honor/|title=Paul McCartney awarded French Legion of Honor|date=8 September 2012|publisher=SBS News|accessdate=25 October 2012|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121028153134/http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-207_162-57508880/paul-mccartney-awarded-french-legion-of-honor|archivedate=28 October 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
* 2012: [[MusiCares Person of the Year]]

He was appointed [[Member of the Order of the Companions of Honour]] (CH) in the [[2017 Birthday Honours]] for services to music.<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=61962|supp=y|page=B25|date=17 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-merseyside-40306551|title=Queens Birthday Honours: McCartney a Companion of Honour|author=|date=16 June 2017|publisher=|accessdate=27 June 2017|via=www.bbc.com|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170702065547/http://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-merseyside-40306551|archivedate=2 July 2017|df=dmy-all|newspaper=BBC News}}</ref>

